result.execSummary:
The defendant Tia L. Bourdo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

1:03 pm case called. Defendant Tia L. Bourdo in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Tia L. Bourdo in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Personal appearance of defendant waived.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.      Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Guilty   Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court sentences the defendant to: 1 days WCJ, with credit for 1 days served. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal Rights faxed to WCJ.
Bond poster's address returned by USPS - Moved, left no address - Unable to Forward

Case called @ 2:46 p.m. Defendant Tia L. Bourdo not in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Base on non appearance the Court authorizes the issuance of a bench warrant extraditable within the State of Wisconsin. The Court orders the $250 cash bond forfeited.
No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Case Called @ 3:22 PM: Defendant Tia L. Bourdo in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.
